						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is damaged and built in and also incomplete. It begins with the introduction <hi rend="italic">Tirumagaḷpōla</hi> etc. It seems to record an endowment of land made by the <hi rend="italic">Sabhā</hi> of Tirumeyyam a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna-brahmadēya</hi> village in Kāṉa-nāḍu said to be a division of Arumoḻidēva-vaḷanāḍu to provide for worship and offerings to god Vishṇu-Bhaṭāraka consecreted in the temple of Śrī Mūlasthānam-uḍaiya Mahādēva by a resident of the place by name Tiruvēṅgaḍa[Tātar]. </p>						

						</summary>
